        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 1:57AM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 157 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Severance, or 9 miles east of Fort Collins, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Eastern Fort Collins, Windsor, Eaton, Severance, Ault, Pierce,
Timnath, Nunn, Black Hollow Reservoir and New Windsor Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
